headline: 3 Reliable Dividend Stocks Yielding At Least 3%
summary: Despite a recent U.S. government shutdown and unexpected job losses, major stock indexes like the Dow Jones Industrial Average have shown resilience, with the S&P 500 and Nasdaq maintaining upward momentum. In such an unpredictable environment, dividend stocks yielding at least 3% can offer stability and income potential for investors seeking reliable returns amidst market volatility.
